<p><i><b>The History of the Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire</b></i> (known popularly as <i><b>The History</b></i>) was written by <a href="/wiki/England" title="England">English</a> <a href="/wiki/Historian" title="Historian">historian</a> <a href="/wiki/Edward_Gibbon" title="Edward Gibbon">Edward Gibbon</a> and published in six volumes. Volume I was published in <a href="/wiki/1776" title="1776">1776</a>, and went through six printings. Volumes II and III were published in <a href="/wiki/1781" title="1781">1781</a>; volumes IV, V, VI in <a href="/wiki/1788" title="1788">1788</a>-<a href="/wiki/1789" title="1789">89</a>. The original volumes were published as <a href="/wiki/Quarto_(text)" title="Quarto (text)">quartos</a>, a common publishing practice of the time. It stands as a major literary achievement of the <a href="/wiki/18th_century" title="18th century">18th century</a> because it was adopted as a model for the methodologies of modern historians. This led to Gibbon being called the first modern historian of Ancient Rome.</p>
